      "name": "coconut oil",
      "amount": "1 tbsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "salt",
      "amount": "1 tsp"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Rinse the fermented lentils and drain well.",
    "Heat the coconut oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion, garlic, and ginger and saute until the onion is translucent.",
    "Add the curry powder and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the lentils, vegetable broth, and salt, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes, or until the lentils are tender.",
    "Stir in the shredded coconut.",
    "Transfer the curry to a hot stone plate and broil for 2 minutes, or until the top is lightly browned.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy."
  ],
